    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Ok, how much did you hate having to do the <code class=\"language-text\">zz</code>?  It is annoying.  Instead,\nlets tell vim to do it for us.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"viml\"><pre class=\"language-viml\"><code class=\"language-viml\">:set scrolloff=8</code></pre></div>\n<p>Now lets scroll around.  How does it feel.  SO GOOD.</p>\n<hr>\n<p>Lets quit out of our previous vim experience and curl down this file.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">curl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ThePrimeagen/vim-fundamentals/master/course-website/lessons/some-javascript.md > exercise.js &amp;&amp; vim exercise.js</code></pre></div>\n<p>After following the delete instructions you should notice that its really hard\nto count how many lines of code huh? Type the following</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"viml\"><pre class=\"language-viml\"><code class=\"language-viml\">:set number</code></pre></div>\n<p>You will notice a new column has been added and now you have line numbers!\nYeah its pretty easy to a jump, but also not all that easy.  Math can be hard\nsometimes.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"viml\"><pre class=\"language-viml\"><code class=\"language-viml\">&quot; sets relative numbers\n:set relativenumber\n\n&quot; turns off relative numbers\n:set norelativenumber</code></pre></div>\n<p>Wow.  Much better huh?  You can jump easily now.  You may not be good at\njumping yet, but you can see its a lot easier.  Lets play around.</p>\n<p>Put your cursor on <code class=\"language-text\">foo</code> and press <code class=\"language-text\">v10j</code>.  What happened?  Press <code class=\"language-text\">V</code> to\nhighlight the whole line.</p>\n<p>Ok lets leave vim, <code class=\"language-text\">:q</code> and reopen back up the file either by reexecuting the\ncurl command or simply executing <code class=\"language-text\">vim exercise.js</code></p>\n<p>What happened?</p>\n<p>Commands you execute only live for the session you have vim open.  This is\npainful right?  Well, actually not.  There is a <code class=\"language-text\">.vimrc</code>!  All is not horrible.\nSo lets create one!</p>\n<p>Create a vimrc in the correct location with the following content.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"viml\"><pre class=\"language-viml\"><code class=\"language-viml\">set scrolloff=8\nset number\nset relativenumber</code></pre></div>\n<p>Open up vim again.  Ohh yeah!  This is great, but those tabs have to go (tabs\nvs spaces anyone?)!  Add these lines to your vimrc and restart vim.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"viml\"><pre class=\"language-viml\"><code class=\"language-viml\">set tabstop=4 softtabstop=4\nset shiftwidth=4\nset expandtab\nset smartindent</code></pre></div>\n<p>Now restart vim... what just happened?  Pretty cool huh?</p>\n<h3 id=\"how-do-you-know-what-is-available\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#how-do-you-know-what-is-available\" aria-label=\"how do you know what is available permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>How do you know what is available?</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>You can google.  Sometimes that is a good thing.</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">h options</code></li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">h &lt;tabcomplete or ctrl-d></code></li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">h &lt;specific option name></code></li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"path":"/vim-my-way","title":"Vim My Way","order":"9A","section":"The VimRC","description":"Ok, so vim looked pretty ugly.  Lets make it feel the way we want it!"}},"allMarkdownRemark":{"edges":[{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"53A","path":"/pit-stop","title":"Pit Stop"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"54A","path":"/adv-motions","title":"Advanced Motions"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"50A","path":"/search-and-replace","title":"Search And Replace"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"51A","path":"/macros","title":"Macros"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"52A","path":"/registers","title":"Registers"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"3A","path":"/are-you-ready","title":"Are You Ready?"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"5A","path":"/basic-usage","title":"Using Vim"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"10A","path":"/color-my-pencils","title":"Color My Pencils"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"69A","path":"/exercise-0","title":"hjkl-x"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"70A","path":"/exercise-1","title":"dyp"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"71A","path":"/exercise-2","title":"insert"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"72A","path":"/exercise-3","title":"Search and Replace"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"73A","path":"/exercise-4","title":"Macros"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"74A","path":"/exercise-5","title":"Registers"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"75A","path":"/exercise-6","title":"Advanced Motions"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"15A","path":"/files-e","title":"Files and Navigations - Edit"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"11A","path":"/files","title":"Files and Navigations"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"16A","path":"/files-marks","title":"Files and Navigations - Marks"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"12A","path":"/files-netrw","title":"Files and Navigations - NetRW"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"17A","path":"/files-recap","title":"Files and Navigations - Recap"}}},{"node":{"